cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DS

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with the analysis of neural data using multi-electrode arrays. It also involves the use of GPGPU (General-Purpose Graphics Processing Unit) for real-time data mining, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of two-pass elimination approach, which is a common technique in data mining and falls under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper mentions the evaluation of the approach on both synthetic and real datasets, which involves the use of computer vision techniques and falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
